This folder contains all R scripts used to simulate, process, and visualise gene drive scenarios for the one locus MEREA system.

The directory is structured to separate gene drive configurations (e.g. bisex vs two-locus) and script functionality (e.g. simulation vs plotting vs data preparation).

üìÅ Subdirectories:
  
- two_loci/
    ‚Ü≥ two_loci_actual_frequency.R   : Simulates idealised (mathematically simplified) two-locus gene drive releases
    ‚Ü≥ two_loci_realistic_frequency.R: Simulates ecologically realistic scenarios including larval carryover and overlapping generations

- plots/
    ‚Ü≥ two_loci_thresholds_all.R     : Visualises suppression success vs introduction threshold for two_locus
    ‚Ü≥ two_loci_heatmap.R            : Visualises surviving wildtype females across all thresholds and all releases

- dataframe/
    ‚Ü≥ realistic_two_loci_combined.R : Prepares and combines realistic simulation outputs into a unified data frame
    ‚Ü≥ actual_two_loci_combined.R    : Prepares combined output for idealised bisex scenarios